  "lambda^2": "lambda^2",
  "det(A - lambda I) = (0 - lambda)(0 - lambda) - (-1)(1) = lambda^2 + 1. This is a 90-degree rotation matrix with complex eigenvalues i and -i.": "det(A - lambda I) = (0 - lambda) (0 - lambda) - (-1)(1) = lambda^2 + 1. Esta es una matriz de rotaciĂłn de 90 grados con valores propios complejos i y -i.",
  "What is the characteristic polynomial of a matrix?": "ÂżCuĂĄl es el polinomio caracterĂ­stico de una matriz?",
  "A polynomial representing the trace as a function of lambda": "Un polinomio que representa el rastro en funciĂłn de lambda",
  "A polynomial obtained from det(A - lambda I) whose roots are the eigenvalues": "Polinomio obtenido de det(A - lambda I) cuyas raĂ­ces son los valores propios",
  "A polynomial whose roots give the singular values of the matrix": "Un polinomio cuyas raĂ­ces dan los valores singulares de la matriz",
  "The minimal polynomial that annihilates the matrix": "El polinomio mĂ­nimo que aniquila la matriz",
  "The characteristic polynomial is p(lambda) = det(A - lambda I). Its roots are precisely the eigenvalues of the matrix A.": "El polinomio caracterĂ­stico es p(lambda) = det(A - lambda I). Sus raĂ­ces son precisamente los valores propios de la matriz A.",
  "What does the term 'algebraic multiplicity' mean for an eigenvalue?": "ÂżQuĂŠ significa el tĂŠrmino 'multiplicaciĂłn algebraica' para un valor propio?",
  "The number of times the eigenvalue appears as a root of the characteristic polynomial": "El nĂşmero de veces que el valor propio aparece como una raĂ­z del polinomio caracterĂ­stico",
  "The dimension of the eigenspace associated with that eigenvalue": "La dimensiĂłn del espacio propio asociado con ese valor propio",
  "The number of eigenvectors corresponding to that eigenvalue": "El nĂşmero de autovectores correspondiente a ese valor propio",
  "The absolute value of the eigenvalue": "El valor absoluto del valor propio",
  "The algebraic multiplicity of an eigenvalue is the number of times it appears as a root of the characteristic polynomial, counting repeated roots.": "La multiplicidad algebraica de un valor propio es el nĂşmero de veces que aparece como raĂ­z del polinomio caracterĂ­stico, contando raĂ­ces repetidas.",
  "What is the trace of a matrix in relation to its characteristic polynomial?": "ÂżCuĂĄl es el rastro de una matriz en relaciĂłn con su polinomio caracterĂ­stico?",
  "The trace has no relationship to the characteristic polynomial": "El rastro no tiene relaciĂłn con el polinomio caracterĂ­stico",
  "The trace equals the constant term of the characteristic polynomial": "El rastro es igual al tĂŠrmino constante del polinomio caracterĂ­stico",
  "The trace equals the sum of the roots of the characteristic polynomial": "El rastro es igual a la suma de las raĂ­ces del polinomio caracterĂ­stico",
  "The trace equals the leading coefficient of the characteristic polynomial": "El rastro es igual al coeficiente principal del polinomio caracterĂ­stico",
  "The trace of a matrix equals the sum of its eigenvalues, which are the roots of the characteristic polynomial. For an n x n matrix, the coefficient of lambda^(n-1) equals (-1) times the trace.": "El rastro de una matriz es igual a la suma de sus valores propios, que son las raĂ­ces del polinomio caracterĂ­stico. Para una matriz n x n, el coeficiente de lambda^(n-1) es igual a (-1) veces el rastro.",
  "What does the Cayley-Hamilton theorem state?": "ÂżQuĂŠ dice el teorema Cayley-Hamilton?",
  "Every matrix has at least one real eigenvalue": "Cada matriz tiene al menos un valor propio real",
  "The characteristic polynomial always has distinct roots": "El polinomio caracterĂ­stico siempre tiene raĂ­ces distintas",
  "Similar matrices have different characteristic polynomials": "Matrices similares tienen polinomios caracterĂ­sticos diferentes",
  "Every matrix satisfies its own characteristic polynomial": "Cada matriz satisface su propio polinomio caracterĂ­stico",
  "The Cayley-Hamilton theorem states that every square matrix satisfies its own characteristic equation. If p(lambda) is the characteristic polynomial of A, then p(A) = 0 (the zero matrix).": "El teorema de Cayley-Hamilton afirma que cada matriz cuadrada satisface su propia ecuaciĂłn caracterĂ­stica. Si p(lambda) es el polinomio caracterĂ­stico de A, entonces p(A) = 0 (la matriz cero).",
  "What is a 'monic polynomial' in the context of characteristic polynomials?": "ÂżQuĂŠ es un polinomio monico en el contexto de los polinomios caracterĂ­sticos?",
  "A polynomial whose highest-degree term has coefficient 1": "Polinomio cuyo tĂŠrmino de grado mĂĄs alto tiene coeficiente 1",
