  "A polynomial whose leading coefficient is 1 or -1": "Un polinomio cuyo coeficiente principal es 1 o -1",
  "A polynomial with all positive coefficients": "Un polinomio con todos los coeficientes positivos",
  "A monic polynomial has a leading coefficient of 1. Characteristic polynomials are often written in monic form as lambda^n - (trace)lambda^(n-1) + ... + (-1)^n det(A).": "Un polinomio mĂłnico tiene un coeficiente principal de 1. Los polinomios caracterĂ­sticos se escriben a menudo en forma mĂłnica como lambda^n - (trace)lambda^(n-1) + ... + (-1)^n det(A).",
  "What is the minimal polynomial of a matrix?": "ÂżCuĂĄl es el polinomio mĂ­nimo de una matriz?",
  "The characteristic polynomial divided by the determinant": "El polinomio caracterĂ­stico dividido por el determinante",
  "The monic polynomial of least degree that annihilates the matrix": "El polinomio mĂłnico de menor grado que aniquila la matriz",
  "The polynomial with the smallest coefficients that has the same roots": "El polinomio con los coeficientes mĂĄs pequeĂąos que tiene las mismas raĂ­ces",
  "The polynomial formed by the smallest eigenvalue only": "El polinomio formado por el valor propio mĂĄs pequeĂąo sĂłlo",
  "The minimal polynomial is the monic polynomial of smallest degree such that p(A) = 0. It always divides the characteristic polynomial and shares the same roots.": "El polinomio mĂ­nimo es el polinomio mĂłnico de menor grado tal que p(A) = 0. Siempre divide el polinomio caracterĂ­stico y comparte las mismas raĂ­ces.",
  "What is the 'characteristic equation' of a matrix?": "ÂżCuĂĄl es la 'ecuaciĂłn caracterĂ­stica' de una matriz?",
  "The equation Ax = b for an unknown vector x": "La ecuaciĂłn Ax = b para un vector desconocido x",
  "The equation det(A) = 0": "La ecuaciĂłn det(A) = 0",
