  "det(K - lambda I) = (5 - lambda)(3 - lambda) - (-2)(-2) = lambda^2 - 8lambda + 15 - 4 = lambda^2 - 8lambda + 11. The roots give the squares of the natural frequencies.": "det(K - lambda I) = (5 - lambda) (3 - lambda) - (-2)-2) = lambda^2 - 8lambda + 15 - 4 = lambda^2 - 8lambda + 11. Las raĂ­ces dan los cuadrados de las frecuencias naturales.",
  "A population biologist models two competing species with the matrix A = [[1.2, -0.3], [0.1, 0.8]]. To analyze long-term behavior, she computes the characteristic polynomial. What is the sum of the eigenvalues?": "Un biĂłlogo poblacional modela dos especies competidoras con la matriz A = [[1.2, -0.3], [0.1, 0.8]. Para analizar el comportamiento a largo plazo, ella calcula el polinomio caracterĂ­stico. ÂżCuĂĄl es la suma de los valores propios?",
  "0.96": "0,96",
  "2.0": "2.0",
  "1.5": "1.5",
  "0.4": "0,4",
  "The sum of the eigenvalues equals the trace of A. trace(A) = 1.2 + 0.8 = 2.0. This is the coefficient of lambda in the characteristic polynomial (with a sign change).": "La suma de los valores propios es igual a la traza de A. trace(A) = 1.2 + 0.8 = 2.0. Este es el coeficiente de lambda en el polinomio caracterĂ­stico (con un cambio de signo).",
  "A control systems engineer analyzes the stability of a feedback system with matrix A = [[0, 1], [-6, -5]]. Using the characteristic polynomial, what are the eigenvalues?": "Un ingeniero de sistemas de control analiza la estabilidad de un sistema de retroalimentaciĂłn con matriz A = [[0, 1], [-6, -5]]. Usando el polinomio caracterĂ­stico, ÂżcuĂĄles son los valores propios?",
