  "A chemical engineer models a two-reactor system with the rate matrix A = [[-3, 1], [2, -4]]. She uses the Cayley-Hamilton theorem to express A^(-1) in terms of A and I. If the characteristic polynomial is lambda^2 + 7lambda + 10, what is A^(-1)?": "Un ingeniero quĂ­mico modela un sistema de dos reactores con la matriz de velocidad A = [[-3, 1], [2, -4]]. Utiliza el teorema de Cayley-Hamilton para expresar A^(-1) en tĂŠrminos de A e I. Si el polinomio caracterĂ­stico es lambda^2 + 7lambda + 10, ÂżquĂŠ es A^(-1)?",
