  "det(H - lambda I) = (2-lambda)(4-lambda) - (-1)(1) = 8 - 6lambda + lambda^2 + 1 = lambda^2 - 6lambda + 9 = (lambda - 3)^2. The repeated eigenvalue 3 indicates a critically damped system.": "det(H - lambda I) = (2-lambda)(4-lambda) - (-1)(1) = 8 - 6lambda + lambda^2 + 1 = lambda^2 - 6lambda + 9 = (lambda - 3)^2. El autovalor 3 repetido indica un sistema de amortiguaciĂłn crĂ­tica.",
  "A wildlife biologist uses a Leslie matrix L = [[0, 4], [0.5, 0]] to model a fish population. What is the dominant eigenvalue (largest in absolute value)?": "Un biĂłlogo de vida silvestre utiliza una matriz Leslie L = [[0, 4], [0,5, 0]] para modelar una poblaciĂłn de peces. ÂżCuĂĄl es el valor propio dominante (mĂĄs grande en valor absoluto)?",
